# Katana (Web Crawling & Spidering)

## Basic Crawling
`katana -u https://target.com`
`katana -list targets.txt`

## Depth and Scope
`katana -u https://target.com -d 3`
`katana -u https://target.com -jc`

## Headless Mode (JavaScript Rendering)
`katana -u https://target.com -hl`
`katana -u https://target.com -hl -sc`

## Filtering and Extraction
`katana -u https://target.com -em php,js,json`
`katana -u https://target.com -f qurl`
`katana -u https://target.com -mr "admin|dashboard"`

## Headers and Authentication
`katana -u https://target.com -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>"`
`katana -u https://target.com -H "Cookie: session=abc1234"`

## Proxies and Rate Limiting
`katana -u https://target.com -proxy http://127.0.0.1:8080`
`katana -u https://target.com -rl 150`
`katana -u https://target.com -c 20`

## Output
`katana -u https://target.com -o crawled_urls.txt`
`katana -u https://target.com -j -o crawled_urls.json`

## Common Flags
* `-u` - Target URL to crawl
* `-list` - File containing a list of target URLs
* `-d` - Maximum depth to crawl (default 3)
* `-hl` - Enable headless mode (uses a real browser to execute JavaScript and find hidden links)
* `-jc` - Enable JavaScript parsing/crawling (extracts endpoints from JS files)
* `-em` - Extension match; only show results with these extensions (e.g., `js,php`)
* `-f` - Field extraction (e.g., `qurl` to only print URLs with query parameters)
* `-mr` - Match regex; only print URLs matching this pattern
* `-H` - Add custom headers to requests
* `-c` - Number of concurrent fetchers/threads (default 10)
* `-rl` - Rate limit in requests per second (default 150)
* `-proxy` - Route traffic through a proxy (useful for sending discovered endpoints directly to Burp Suite)
* `-o` - File to write output
* `-j` - Output in JSON Lines (JSONL) format
* `-sc` - Print HTTP status codes alongside the URLs
